{
  "local_port": 54250,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the various non-tech companies that visit N.S.I.T for placements and what is the skill set that they are looking for in a person?",
  "response": "At **Netaji Subhas Institute of Technology (NSIT), Delhi**, a wide range of non-tech companies visit for placements, spanning sectors like **consulting, finance, FMCG (Fast-Moving Consumer Goods), core engineering, analytics, and more**. These companies look for a combination of **technical, analytical, and soft skills** in candidates, depending on the role and industry. Below is an overview of the non-tech companies and the skill sets they typically seek:\n\n---\n\n### **Non-Tech Companies Visiting NSIT (Examples)**\n\n1. **Management Consulting Firms:**\n   - McKinsey & Company\n   - Boston Consulting Group (BCG)\n   - Bain & Company  \n   *Roles:* Business Analyst, Consultant  \n   *Skills:* Problem-solving, analytical thinking, communication, strategic mindset, case-solving ability.\n\n2. **Finance and Investment Banking:**\n   - Goldman Sachs\n   - JP Morgan\n   - Deutsche Bank  \n   *Roles:* Analyst, Investment Banker, Risk Analyst  \n   *Skills:* Quantitative aptitude, financial modeling, analytical reasoning, attention to detail, communication.\n\n3. **FMCG Companies:**\n   - Hindustan Unilever Limited (HUL)\n   - ITC\n   - Procter & Gamble (P&G)  \n   *Roles:* Sales & Marketing, Supply Chain, Management Trainee  \n   *Skills:* Leadership, communication, problem-solving, creativity, business acumen.\n\n4. **Analytics and Data-Driven Firms:**\n   - Fractal Analytics\n   - Mu Sigma\n   - American Express  \n   *Roles:* Data Analyst, Business Analyst  \n   *Skills:* Data interpretation, statistical analysis, programming (Python, R), logical reasoning, presentation skills.\n\n5. **Core Engineering and Manufacturing:**\n   - Larsen & Toubro (L&T)\n   - Tata Motors\n   - General Electric (GE)  \n   *Roles:* Engineer Trainee, Management Trainee  \n   *Skills:* Core technical knowledge, problem-solving, communication, adaptability.\n\n6. **E-commerce and Retail:**\n   - Amazon\n   - Flipkart\n   *Roles:* Operations Manager, Business Analyst  \n   *Skills:* Analytical thinking, logistics knowledge, problem-solving, communication.\n\n7. **Government and Public Sector Units (PSUs):**\n   - ONGC\n   - BHEL\n   - NTPC  \n   *Roles:* Engineer Trainee, Management Trainee  \n   *Skills:* Technical knowledge, problem-solving, general aptitude.\n\n---\n\n### **Skill Sets Non-Tech Companies Look For**\n\n1. **Analytical and Problem-Solving Skills:**\n   - Ability to analyze data, interpret trends, and solve complex problems.\n   - Strong quantitative aptitude for roles in finance and analytics.\n\n2. **Communication and Presentation Skills:**\n   - Clear and concise communication, both written and verbal.\n   - Ability to present ideas effectively.\n\n3. **Leadership and Teamwork:**\n   - Demonstrated leadership experience (e.g., college clubs, projects).\n   - Ability to work collaboratively in teams.\n\n4. **Business Acumen and Strategic Thinking:**\n   - Understanding of market trends and business strategies.\n   - Ability to think critically and make data-driven decisions.\n\n5. **Adaptability and Learning Agility:**\n   - Willingness to learn new skills and adapt to dynamic environments.\n\n6. **Technical Proficiency:**\n   - Basic programming knowledge (Python, SQL, Excel) for analytics roles.\n   - Core technical knowledge for engineering and manufacturing roles.\n\n7. **Soft Skills:**\n   - Time management, work ethic, and interpersonal skills.\n\n---\n\n### **Preparation Tips for Students**\n1. **Case Study Preparation:** For consulting roles, practice case interviews.\n2. **Quantitative Aptitude:** For finance and analytics roles, focus on math, puzzles, and logical reasoning.\n3. **Mock Interviews:** Practice behavioral and technical interviews.\n4. **Networking:** Leverage alumni and LinkedIn connections for insights.\n5. **Resume Building:** Highlight relevant internships, projects, and leadership experiences.\n\nBy focusing on these skill sets and preparing accordingly, NSIT students can increase their chances of securing placements in non-tech companies.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
